OL,7,FThe jury previously heard how two boys
OL,8,Fwere asleep in cabin-style beds in one
OL,9,Fof the school's boarding houses when
OL,10,Fthe defendant climbed up and attacked
OL,11,Fthem shortly before 1am on 9 June last
OL,12,Fyear.
OL,14,FHousemaster Henry Roffe-Silvester, who
OL,15,Fwas asleep in his own quarters, was
OL,16,Fawoken by noises coming from the
OL,17,Fboarding house and went to investigate.
