OL,7,FThe boy said, on one occasion, the
OL,8,Fdefendant took pictures of him as he
OL,9,Fchanged his clothes, which he asked
OL,10,Fhim to delete.
OL,12,FOn other occasions the defendant did
OL,13,Fnot "respect" the boy's belongings and
OL,14,Fwould damage them while he was away,
OL,15,Fthe court heard.
OL,17,F"There were sometimes when he could be
OL,18,Fa normal person and just nice," the
OL,19,Fboy told police.
