OL,7,FAsked how he made him feel, the boy
OL,8,Fsaid: "Why did he choose to be unkind
OL,9,Fto people when he used to be nice?
OL,11,F"I had known him in year nine and what
OL,12,Fgood friends we had been. It was a
OL,13,Fshame he turned against me."
OL,15,FThe court heard teaching staff carried
OL,16,Fout searches of dormitories after
OL,17,Fitems were going missing at the school
OL,18,Fand discovered the defendant kept a
OL,19,Fhammer.
